    {
        "content": "<p>fitzgen <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13421#issuecomment-4502385897\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13421\">PR #13421</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Would this perhaps make sense to be a <code>misc</code> fuzz target?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Unfortunately it can't because it requires setting up its own global allocator.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also, could you land a change in upstream oss-fuzz passing the <code>--cfg</code> necessary before landing this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yep, that is <a href=\"https://github.com/google/oss-fuzz/pull/15532\">https://github.com/google/oss-fuzz/pull/15532</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
